<item>
            <title>[IMAGING-199] All tEXt chunks are not returned from PngImageParser.getMetadata</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/IMAGING-199</link>
                <project id="12313421" key="IMAGING">Commons Imaging</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;According to the PNG spec - Section 4.2.3 - Textual Information -&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;Any number of text chunks can appear, and more than one with the same keyword is permissible. &quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Unfortunately the PngImageParser.getMetadata method only supports a single tEXt chunk.  The problem is in the following line:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;        final List&amp;lt;PngChunk&amp;gt; chunks = readChunks(byteSource, new ChunkType[] &lt;/p&gt;
{ ChunkType.tEXt, ChunkType.zTXt, }
&lt;p&gt;, true);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;True is being passed for returnAfterFirst. I believe that false should be passed instead.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I can submit a pull request if you agree.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
